&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADULT MENTAL HEALTH DIRECTORATE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOUTH LEICESTERSHIRE COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH TEAM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RECEPTIONIST/ADMIN ASSISTANT REQUIRED BAND 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Cedars Centre&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cedar Avenue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wigston, Leics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LE18 2LA &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: £18,005 - £19,337 pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time Post– Monday – Friday Mornings 22.5 hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A friendly, highly motivated, enthusiastic individual is required as a Receptionist/Admin Assistant to support the Community Mental Health Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to good reception skills and experience of word processing, a sympathetic and confident telephone manner is essential. You must be a good communicator, well organised and able to work as part of a team as well as on your own initiative. You will be required to provide Reception duties as well as run Outpatient Clinics on a daily basis. If you have NVQ Level 2 or equivalent in Customer Care along with previous experience of working within a similar environment then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this post and would like further details, please contact Bev Mason, Admin Manager on 0116 2255700 for an informal chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job description and application forms are available from the NHS Jobs Website.&lt;/p&gt;
